---
layout: base.njk
title: Web Everything — Plugs
---

<section class="intro">
  <h1>Plugs</h1>
  <p>
    Plugs are <strong>speculative platform primitives</strong> — runtime building blocks (registries,
    base classes, injectors) that imagine how a missing capability would fit if it were normalized into
    the web platform. Each plug below links to its full specification.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="content-box plug-stance" style="margin: 0 0 2rem;">
  <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">What a plug is — and isn't</h2>
  <p>
    Every plug is designed by asking one question: <strong>"what if this were a standard?"</strong> Each one
    imagines how a missing capability would fit <em>if it were normalized into the web platform</em>, and we
    build it that way in the hope it aligns with where standards are actually heading.
  </p>
  <p>
    That's the design lens, not a claim of authority. We depend on <strong>no adoption</strong> — a plug runs
    today as a standalone library whether or not any of it ever ships natively. And we stay humble: we are
    <strong>not crowning ourselves the future standard</strong>. The aspiration is to <em>inform</em>
    standardization by exploring the shape a primitive could take — nothing here is gated on the platform
    agreeing with us.
  </p>
</section>

<section style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;">
  <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 220px; max-width: 420px;">
    <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 0.85em; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--color-text-muted);">Search</h3>
    <input type="search" id="plug-search" placeholder="Filter by name, summary, or type…"
           style="width: 100%; padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.9em; background: var(--color-surface, #fff);">
  </div>
</section>

<div class="project-grid" id="plug-grid">
  {% for plug in plugs %}
  <a href="/plugs/{{ plug.id }}/"
     class="project-card plug-tile"
     data-haystack="{{ plug.id }} {{ plug.name | lower }} {{ plug.summary | lower }} {{ plug.type | lower }}"
     style="text-decoration: none; color: inherit; display: block;">
    <div class="project-header" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
      <h3 class="project-title" style="margin: 0;">{{ plug.name }}</h3>
      <span style="padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 9999px; background: {% if plug.status == 'active' %}#dcfce7{% elif plug.status == 'draft' %}#dbeafe{% elif plug.status == 'concept' %}#fef3c7{% elif plug.status == 'experimental' %}#fde68a{% else %}#f1f5f9{% endif %}; color: {% if plug.status == 'active' %}#166534{% elif plug.status == 'draft' %}#1e40af{% elif plug.status == 'concept' %}#92400e{% elif plug.status == 'experimental' %}#854d0e{% else %}#475569{% endif %}; font-size: 0.75em; font-weight: 600; white-space: nowrap;">{{ plug.status | title }}</span>
    </div>
    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9em;">{{ plug.summary | safe }}</p>
  </a>
  {% endfor %}
</div>

<p id="plug-empty" style="display: none; text-align: center; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: 2rem 0;">No plugs match.</p>

<script>
(function () {
  var grid = document.getElementById('plug-grid');
  var empty = document.getElementById('plug-empty');
  var search = document.getElementById('plug-search');
  var tiles = Array.prototype.slice.call(grid.querySelectorAll('.plug-tile'));
  search.addEventListener('input', function () {
    var q = (search.value || '').trim().toLowerCase();
    var visible = 0;
    tiles.forEach(function (tile) {
      var ok = !q || tile.dataset.haystack.indexOf(q) !== -1;
      tile.style.display = ok ? '' : 'none';
      if (ok) visible++;
    });
    empty.style.display = visible === 0 ? '' : 'none';
  });
})();
</script>
